  "response_text": "# Weekly Dorm-Friendly Meal & Fitness Plan\n\n## KITCHEN SETUP (Minimal)\n- Microwave, mini-fridge, hot plate/electric kettle\n- Basic utensils, cutting board, sharp knife\n- Storage containers\n\n---\n\n## MONDAY\n\n**Meals:**\n- **Breakfast:** Overnight oats (oats + milk + banana, made night before)\n- **Lunch:** Deli turkey sandwich + apple + almonds\n- **Dinner:** Microwaved rice bowl (instant rice + canned black beans + salsa)\n- **Snack:** Greek yogurt + granola\n\n**Fitness:**\n- 20 min: Dorm room circuit (no equipment)\n  - 10 push-ups\n  - 15 bodyweight squats\n  - 30-sec plank\n  - Repeat 4x\n\n---\n\n## TUESDAY\n\n**Meals:**\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs + toast (hot plate)\n- **Lunch:** Tuna salad (canned tuna + mayo + crackers)\n- **Dinner:** Pasta with jarred marinara + frozen veggies\n- **Snack:** String cheese + berries\n\n**Fitness:**\n- 30 min: Walk/jog campus or nearby park\n- 10 min: Stretching in room\n\n---\n\n## WEDNESDAY\n\n**Meals:**\n- **Breakfast:** Cereal + milk + banana\n- **Lunch:** Peanut butter & jelly sandwich + carrot sticks\n- **Dinner:** Microwaved sweet potato + canned chickpeas + olive oil\n- **Snack:** Popcorn (microwave packets)\n\n**Fitness:**\n- 25 min: YouTube HIIT workout (bodyweight)\n- Core focus: planks, mountain climbers, leg raises\n\n---\n\n## THURSDAY\n\n**Meals:**\n- **Breakfast:** Instant oatmeal with cinnamon + berries\n- **Lunch:** Rotisserie chicken (store-bought) + rice + broccoli (microwaved)\n- **Dinner:** Quesadilla (tortilla + cheese + canned beans, hot plate)\n- **Snack:** Trail mix + apple\n\n**Fitness:**\n- 20 min: Strength focus\n  - Tricep dips (using chair)\n  - Wall sits\n  - Lunges\n  - Repeat 3x\n\n---\n\n## FRIDAY\n\n**Meals:**\n- **Breakfast:** Yogurt parfait (yogurt + granola + honey)\n- **Lunch:** Egg salad sandwich + grapes\n- **Dinner:** Ramen upgraded (add frozen veggies, egg, hot sauce)\n- **Snack:** Hummus + pita chips\n\n**Fitness:**\n- 30 min: Walk/explore campus or light cardio video\n- Rest/recovery focus\n\n---\n\n## SATURDAY\n\n**Meals:**\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs + avocado toast\n- **Lunch:** Meal prep day—make 3 mason jar salads for next week\n- **Dinner:** Treat meal (dining hall, nearby restaurant, or pizza)\n- **Snack:** Chocolate + almonds\n\n**Fitness:**\n- 40 min: Longer walk or recreational activity\n- Yoga/stretching video (20 min)\n\n---\n\n## SUNDAY\n\n**Meals:**\n- **Breakfast:** Pancakes (mix + hot plate) + berries\n- **Lunch:** Leftover protein + veggies from prep\n- **Dinner:** Microwaved burrito bowl (rice + beans + corn + cheese)\n- **Snack:** Fruit + peanut butter\n\n**Fitness:**\n- Active recovery day\n- 15 min: Light stretching/mobility work\n- Optional: 20 min easy walk\n\n---\n\n## GROCERY SHOPPING LIST\n\n**Proteins:**\n- Eggs, Greek yogurt, canned tuna/chickpeas, deli meat, peanut butter\n\n**Grains:**\n- Bread, rice, pasta, oats, cereal, tortillas\n\n**Produce:**\n- Bananas, apples, berries, carrots, frozen broccoli, sweet potatoes\n\n**Pantry:**\n- Olive oil, salt, spices, canned beans, jarred marinara, salsa\n\n**Convenience:**\n- Rotisserie chicken, string cheese, nuts, granola\n\n---\n\n## TIPS FOR SUCCESS\n\n✓ **Prep Sunday:** Cook rice, chop veggies, assemble containers  \n✓ **Buy frozen:** Lasts longer, just as nutritious  \n✓ **Use canned:** Beans, tuna, vegetables—budget-friendly  \n✓ **Fitness alternatives:** YouTube, campus gym, outdoor spaces  \n✓ **Stay hydrated:** Keep water bottle with you  \n✓ **Adjust portions:** Based on your size/activity level  \n✓ **Budget:** ~$10-12/day with smart shopping\n\nThis plan balances nutrition, convenience, and fitness without needing a full kitchen!",
